1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:05,309
An AI Agent can read a longer prompt, carry more history, and still lose the point.

2
00:00:05,259 --> 00:00:08,173
The failure is not always missing information.

3
00:00:08,173 --> 00:00:16,394
Sometimes the decisive instruction is buried under status updates, tool output, examples, and old decisions that all compete for attention.

4
00:00:16,394 --> 00:00:20,028
Anthropic calls the broader solution context engineering.

5
00:00:20,028 --> 00:00:23,230
Prompt engineering asks how to phrase an instruction.

6
00:00:23,230 --> 00:00:31,567
Context engineering asks which information should be available now, which detail should be retrieved later, and which old material should be compressed or removed.

7
00:00:31,567 --> 00:00:36,798
That distinction matters because an Agent's context window is not an unlimited memory vault.

8
00:00:36,798 --> 00:00:39,028
It is a finite attention budget.

9
00:00:39,028 --> 00:00:45,278
Adding more tokens can increase coverage while reducing the relative strength of the signals that should guide the next action.

10
00:00:45,278 --> 00:00:58,394
In this video, you will learn how to manage that budget: choose high-signal instructions, tools, and examples; retrieve detail on demand; preserve coherence across long tasks; and build a six-part context pack you can reuse.
